get.description:
Scopes [control.events:actors.readonly]. Samples of params: Get only one actor and specify fields to return: 
  {"from": 0, "to": 1755540313, "limit":1, "filter":"id,title"} 
 Get first 10 actors with all fields: 
  {"from": 0, "to": 1755540313, "limit":10}

parameters.description:
URL-encoded query string consists of data values (template fields). Also use "search" to find actor by title.  Multiple key-value pairs are separated by '&' (AND) or '||' (OR). To search by nested fields, use a dot, see the second example. To search by actor`s ref see third example.
For fields of type calendar, you can use the symbols '>', '<', '>=', '<='. Example: dateOfBirth>{'startDate':71182800}
Values can be empty string or array to check for empty/non-empty fields. Example: comment!=, data={}, users!=[]
